title: For Sale/Trade:  104-113 year old gun, Stevens Maynard Jr
postcontent: I have a really nice looking Stevens Maynard Jr. Very rare in this condition. It is a single shot 22 break barrel. The lever has to be held up to keep the barrel closed.Maybe that was how they worked...don't know...I wasn't alive in 1910. Nobody at the last gun show could tell me either. I downloaded a schematic and I don't see any spring or anything parts wise that would have held tension on the lever, so I think this is how they worked.  Made from 1903-1912. Very collectible. Bluing and overall condition very nice. Had a couple collectors at the gun show tell me that it was the nicest one they have seen, and they don't see them very often. Still has good bluing, wood is all intact, and the butt plate is there...rare for these.  Will fetch $550-650 when reworked. Really needs very little work. Cash price is $225.  Leaves you room to tinker and double your investment.
